               <head>'Ahdnamah-yi Aurangzeb ba-Muradbakhsh</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of ʿAhd'nāmah-'i Awrangzīb ba-Murād Bakhsh by Sulṭān Muḥammad Awrangzīb Bahādur</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85104368 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85076229 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115922 http://lccn.loc.gov/n2013007835 http://lccn.loc.gov/n81102519" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3997-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658558.0x000001 viaf_60027758">Sulṭān Muḥammad Awrangzīb Bahādur</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658558.0x000001 viaf_60027758" type="supplied">سلطان محمّد اورنگ زيب بهادر</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21940">ʿAhd'nāmah-'i Awrangzīb ba-Murād Bakhsh</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21940">عهد نامهٴ اورنگ زيب بمراد بخش</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Details the terms of a pact (circa 1658) between the Timurid or Mughal princes Murād Bakhsh (then 'Emperor' of Gujarat) and Awrangzīb (succeeded later as Emperor ʿĀlamgīr), principally against their eldest brother, Dārā Shukūh, accused of heresy and the usurpation of Emperor Shāh Jahān's throne (then convalescing from illness)</p>
                        <p>Copy of letter found in the <title>Ādāb-i ʿĀlamgīrī</title>
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Transcribed by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">G. J. Nicholls</persName>, Judge at <name type="place">Farrukhabad</name>, from a manuscript obtained from <name type="place">Agra</name>Copied from an original manuscript belonging to the library of 
